    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A melamine-formaldehyde resin product formerly used as a consolidant in conservation treatment of waterlogged wood. It was retired from the market in the nineteen seventies and has been replaced by a similar resin, Lyofix (TM), produced by Ciba-Geigy, Basel .</Note_Text>
